    <segment id="1" parent="2" relname="preparation">Steve Fuller, of Durham, UK, wrote:-</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="14" relname="span">

&amp;gt;Here&apos;s one indicator of the difference between the US and the UK:
&amp;gt;
&amp;gt;
&amp;gt;I was just listening to BBC-Radio 1, the UK national pop music station, 
&amp;gt;and this week&apos;s call-in topic was announced:
&amp;gt;
&amp;gt;      Is science out of control, and what should be done if it is?
&amp;gt;
&amp;gt;The announcer said that this question was prompted by a recent statement 
&amp;gt;of Steven Hawking&apos;s, to the effect that the world would have been better 
&amp;gt;off if the leading scientists of the 20th century had been born as flies (!).
&amp;gt;
&amp;gt;Now what do you suppose the 12-35 year old set is likely to make of that 
&amp;gt;one? Tune in and find out!</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="15" relname="span">
&amp;gt;
I can&apos;t tune in, Steve, I don&apos;t live there anymore.</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="17" relname="span"> Keep us posted. </segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="18" relname="span">
Frankly I don&apos;t think wiping out the 20th C scientists would have made all
that much difference;</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="16" relname="list"> no atomic power,</segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="16" relname="list"> far less progress in the materials
sciences,</segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="16" relname="list"> probably less on VLSI electronics,</segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="16" relname="list"> but that&apos;s about it.</segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="19" relname="span"> Seems to
me that we&apos;re still working through the shifts in viewpoint occasioned by
Darwin and his explainers.</segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="10" relname="elaboration"> The implications of the fact that we share 98.4%
of our DNA coding with chimpanzees, or that the Enlightenment has finally
died will take a while to trickle through to the hindbrain.</segment>
    <segment id="12" parent="20" relname="span"> So yes, keep us
posted;</segment>
    <segment id="13" parent="12" relname="motivation"> could be interesting.</segment>
